-English
This is where the most basic code is stored.
The MySQL statements are concatenated using formatting functions, which leads to issues with string mismatches. The MySQL code here will be deprecated in the future because the syntax is overly complicated and difficult for individual developers to master. This code was manually written, so it cannot be directly reused.
As for the machine learning module library, it is custom-built and thus far less functional than the scikit-learn library. You may replace it with scikit-learn for easier deployment. This code will be restructured later to support direct replacement and reuse.
The OCR recognition model used here has relatively low accuracy. If you have access to better OCR models or APIs, you may replace them to improve the reliability of verification. I plan to train my own OCR model in the future.
All the code and functional goals here are derived from job requirements for certain positions in China. However, due to educational background limitations, poor self-expression skills and other factors, I have not secured any job offers. I will continue to improve my capabilities, and based on this project, rebuild it using more effective and practical theoretical knowledge with a hybrid C and Python architecture.
Future optimization directions will include integrating deep learning modules. Whether I can complete these optimizations depends on whether I can make a living. Since I am struggling financially and the functions are not fully implemented, this code is open-sourced for learning purposes only — commercial use is strictly prohibited.
The algorithm implementations here are the most basic versions and do not involve advanced algorithms such as the entropy weight method, which is also a goal for future improvement. As an ordinary third-tier undergraduate student, my mathematical logic is not sufficient to explain all algorithms. I built this platform after preliminary study of Machine Learning (the "Watermelon Book") and combined it with my experience in mathematical modeling competitions, for the convenience of later learners.
